# Global Mobile Layout Policy

## Objective

Mobile (<768px) usable width **93–96%** of viewport. One shell, no stacked narrow wrappers.

## Mandatory shell

Use `MobileFullWidthContainer` or `mobileFullWidthContainerClassName` from `@/components/layout/MobileFullWidthContainer`.

```tsx
// GOOD
<MobileFullWidthContainer>...</MobileFullWidthContainer>
<Card className="w-full" />

// BAD on mobile page shells
<div className="mx-auto max-w-md px-4">
<Card className="max-w-sm mx-auto" />
```

Standard classes: `w-full max-w-none px-3 md:mx-auto md:max-w-3xl`

## Do NOT use on mobile page shells

- `max-w-sm`, `max-w-md` without `md:` prefix
- `w-[80%]`, `w-[85%]`, `w-[90%]` for page content
- narrow `mx-auto` + max-width stacks
- duplicate `px-4` inside `AppContent` / `MobileFullWidthContainer`

## Horizontal scroll

`-mx-3 px-3` (`mobileFullWidthScrollBleedClassName`) — aligned to shell gutters only.

## Exceptions

- **Modals/drawers/dialogs**: may keep `max-w-md`
- **Admin/analytics/data tables**: desktop layouts unchanged
- **Chat bubbles**: `max-w-[85%]` etc. OK
- **Inside AppContent** (`/hub`, `/team/:teamId`, …): page root = `w-full` only — no nested `px-3` / `max-w-md` / `mx-auto max-w-3xl`

## Team pages (`src/pages/team/*`, `src/components/team/*`)

- `TeamHome`, manage, members, lineup: outer `w-full`; cards `w-full`
- `TeamPageLayout` uses `mobileFullWidthContainerClassName`
- Do not stack `AppContent` padding + page `px-4` + card margins

## md+ (tablet/desktop)

Keep centered layouts: `md:max-w-3xl` default; wider pages use `mdMaxWidth` prop.
